comments.body:
@jbtrystram `c/storage` stores images in uncompressed format so it can be used for creating container images. This is intentional and part of design of `podman` and `buildah`. 

> Pushing the layered image to quay does compress the layers again, thankfully ! But the resulting digests are different from the original image.

It happens becuase layers are first uncompressed and compressed again with different algo causing change in digest, this is expected behavior when you build a container again.
